summary: Hey, I just wanted to put this out there, if anyone is having issues paying for their ticket to see Captain Marvel, Endgame, or...
body:
Hey, I just wanted to put this out there, if anyone is having issues paying for their ticket to see Captain Marvel, Endgame, or Far From Home this year, please don’t be afraid to hit me up and I can definitely help out!

I understand some people are down on their luck or just don’t have a supportive household, and I really would like to help! Marvel has been an amazing source of escapism for so many people including myself. Even just getting away from the real world for two hours can make so much difference.

summary: i will always be a little upset that the Ant-Man movie wasn’t about Hank and Janet but i’m so grateful we got to see them on the...
body:
i will always be a little upset that the Ant-Man movie wasn’t about Hank and Janet but i’m so grateful we got to see them on the big screen and the acting was so remarkably done you could feel how real their relationship was and i’m so happy they didn’t kill off Janet or Hank because i was so afraid it was going to be a one or the other situation like in How to Train Your Dragon

and to be fair, i think Scott really does fit with the MCU better. i’m just happy we got our Hank and Janet story even if it was in a Scott Lang movie

summary: Do you do angsty, major character death prompts? I've had this stuck in my head. Basically after the first avengers loki was...
question: Do you do angsty, major character death prompts? I've had this stuck in my head. Basically after the first avengers loki was sentenced to death by Odin.  And Thor goes back to earth bc he knew Tony and loki had a thing before and tells him about what's happening. And takes him to asgard so he can say his goodbyes. He and loki have a tearful conversation in his cell. Tony wants to break him out but loki says no but Tony wants to stay with him through the whole thing and watched him be executed.
answer: I don’t do character death at all. That’s the hardest no from me. ^^°

blog.description: Hi! I'm bitter about a lot of things | Call me Fish | Ao3 | Slytherin | NSFW | Multifandom | Pro Snape | Marvel, DC, Harry Potter, Check Please!, Teen Wolf, Tolkien, Sense8, Star Trek, Star Wars, Yuri!!! On Ice, Merlin, American Gods

body:
I’m just so tired..

Of people saying things like “Well if that character chose to wear makeup then let her wear makeup. It’s not a big deal. Some women like wearing makeup. God just let her live!”

…She’s fictional. She didn’t choose shit. The men in the writing room did. And they always choose the Same. Damn. Thing. Female characters are almost never without makeup and it’s ridiculous. Middle of the zombie apocalypse? Not a blemish in sight, bright red lips. Leading a revolution against an oppressive government? Can’t forget that smokey eye.

It’s stupid. I can’t fathom stopping in front of a mirror for 5-30 minutes just to put makeup on during any of those situations because there are more important things going on than whether my face looks acceptable to myself or other people!

If you feel attacked for me criticizing a female character wearing makeup when it would be inconvenient and make no sense to do so, you need to take a step back and ask why?

Are you really so attached to the idea of makeup that you would attack me for saying this? Really? Why is it so important to you? What is your personal stake in this hill you’ve chosen?
